1
00:00:02,686 --> 00:00:04,086
-ONCE UPON A TIME,

2
00:00:04,086 --> 00:00:07,786
THERE WAS A PRINCESS
RAISED BY LOVING PARENTS.

3
00:00:07,786 --> 00:00:12,019
ONE DAY, THE PRINCESS SNUCK PAST
THE GUARD AT THE GATE

4
00:00:12,019 --> 00:00:16,286
AND SLIPPED OUT OF THE CASTLE
FOR THE VERY FIRST TIME.

5
00:00:16,286 --> 00:00:19,286
NO MATTER HOW FAR SHE WENT,
HOWEVER,

6
00:00:19,286 --> 00:00:23,419
OUTSIDE THE CASTLE,
THERE WAS ONLY AN ENDLESS FOREST

7
00:00:23,419 --> 00:00:24,953
AS BLACK AS PITCH.

8
00:00:24,953 --> 00:00:26,619
BEFORE SHE KNEW IT,

9
00:00:26,619 --> 00:00:31,186
THE PRINCESS ENDED UP UNABLE
TO EITHER ESCAPE THE FOREST

10
00:00:31,186 --> 00:00:33,219
OR RETURN TO THE CASTLE.

11
00:00:33,219 --> 00:00:38,819
IN THAT KINGDOM, THE INSIDE OF
THE CASTLE WAS THE ENTIRE WORLD.

12
00:00:40,353 --> 00:00:44,019
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYS ]

13
00:00:54,619 --> 00:00:58,053
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

14
00:02:10,353 --> 00:02:12,553
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S
"WALTZ OF THE FLOWERS" PLAYS ]

15
00:02:29,361 --> 00:02:32,061
[ BELL TOLLING ]

16
00:02:37,428 --> 00:02:39,861
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

17
00:02:42,801 --> 00:02:44,967
-FAKIR CAST DOWN HIS SWORD

18
00:02:44,967 --> 00:02:47,734
AND FOUND SOMETHING
ONLY HE COULD DO.

19
00:02:47,734 --> 00:02:49,267
-I WANT TO PROTECT HIM...

20
00:02:49,267 --> 00:02:51,134
-BECAUSE HE WANTS TO HELP MYTHO.

21
00:02:51,134 --> 00:02:54,534
-...THE PUREHEARTED MYTHO,
WHO'S ALWAYS RISKED HIMSELF.

22
00:02:54,534 --> 00:02:57,534
-NEVER GIVING UP,
NO MATTER HOW MUCH HE'S HURT,

23
00:02:57,534 --> 00:03:02,301
OVERCOMING THE PAINFUL MEMORIES
HE WANTS TO FORGET.

24
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:05,967
FAKIR IS STRONG.

25
00:03:05,967 --> 00:03:08,734
EVEN IF
HE'S NOT CARRYING A SWORD,

26
00:03:08,734 --> 00:03:10,967
FAKIR IS MYTHO'S KNIGHT.

27
00:03:10,967 --> 00:03:13,334
-WHAT'S FAKIR DOING, ZURA?

28
00:03:13,334 --> 00:03:16,801
-HE'S TALKING TO THE OAK TREE
SO HE CAN WRITE A STORY

29
00:03:16,801 --> 00:03:19,201
THAT PROTECTS THE PERSON
WHO'S IMPORTANT TO HIM.

30
00:03:19,201 --> 00:03:20,501
-AH.

31
00:03:20,501 --> 00:03:23,501
-MAYBE FAKIR REALLY DOESN'T
NEED HELP FROM ANYONE

32
00:03:23,501 --> 00:03:25,601
AND CAN PROTECT MYTHO
ALL BY HIMSELF.

33
00:03:25,601 --> 00:03:26,634
[ GASPS ]

34
00:03:26,634 --> 00:03:30,001
-CAN YOU REALLY SAY
YOU LOVE ME?!

35
00:03:30,001 --> 00:03:31,467
-[ GASPS ]

36
00:03:31,467 --> 00:03:35,001
-DOES MYTHO'S HEART JUST KEEP
GETTING MORE AND MORE STAINED

37
00:03:35,001 --> 00:03:38,101
BY THE RAVEN'S BLOOD
SO THAT HE'S MEAN EVEN TO RUE?

38
00:03:38,101 --> 00:03:39,367
POOR RUE.

39
00:03:39,367 --> 00:03:41,367
I'M KIND OF WORRIED ABOUT HER.

40
00:03:41,367 --> 00:03:43,901
I STILL CAN'T
DO ANYTHING HELPFUL, THOUGH.

41
00:03:43,901 --> 00:03:45,201
[ SIGHS ]

42
00:03:45,201 --> 00:03:46,401
-DUCK?
-HUH?

43
00:03:46,401 --> 00:03:48,367
-ARE YOU OKAY, ZURA?
-HUH?

44
00:03:48,367 --> 00:03:51,367
ARE YOU WORRYING ABOUT ME?

45
00:03:51,367 --> 00:03:53,867
THANK YOU. DON'T WORRY.
I'M OKAY.

46
00:03:53,867 --> 00:03:55,367
-OH, GOOD, ZURA.

47
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:57,967
I THOUGHT THE TEACHER
MIGHT GET MAD AT YOU, ZURA.

48
00:03:57,967 --> 00:03:59,067
-WHAT?

49
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:00,701
-YOU'RE SKIPPING SCHOOL
WITH FAKIR, ZURA!

50
00:04:00,701 --> 00:04:02,234
-HUH? WAUGH!

51
00:04:02,234 --> 00:04:03,367
OH, NO!

52
00:04:03,367 --> 00:04:04,367
I CAME HERE
THINKING I'D CHECK ON FAKIR

53
00:04:04,367 --> 00:04:05,467
ON MY WAY TO SCHOOL,

54
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:07,134
BUT IT'S THIS LATE ALREADY
AND -- [ GASPS ]

55
00:04:07,134 --> 00:04:09,767
-[ SIGHS ]
-[ CHUCKLES ] YEAH, SORRY.

56
00:04:09,767 --> 00:04:11,901
COME ON, UZURA. LET'S GET GOING.

57
00:04:11,901 --> 00:04:15,367
-[ GIGGLING ]

58
00:04:19,401 --> 00:04:21,034
[ DRUM BEATING ]

59
00:04:23,067 --> 00:04:25,101
-OKAY, UZURA, SEE YOU LATER.

60
00:04:25,101 --> 00:04:26,534
-AW!

61
00:04:26,534 --> 00:04:27,601
-[ PANTING ]

62
00:04:27,601 --> 00:04:29,534
HUH?
[ POINK! ]

63
00:04:29,534 --> 00:04:31,467
AAH!
[ GROANS ]

64
00:04:31,467 --> 00:04:32,901
WHA-WHAT?

65
00:04:35,901 --> 00:04:37,567
RUE. WHY IS SHE...

66
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:38,834
-RUE, ZURA?

67
00:04:38,834 --> 00:04:42,401
-WHOA! IT'S OPEN!

68
00:04:42,401 --> 00:04:43,601
[ PANTING ]

69
00:04:53,834 --> 00:04:55,267
RUE!
-[ GASPS ]

70
00:04:55,267 --> 00:04:56,267
TUTU.

71
00:04:56,267 --> 00:04:58,101
-W-WERE YOU JUST CRYING?

72
00:04:58,101 --> 00:05:01,234
-OF COURSE NOT.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

73
00:05:01,234 --> 00:05:03,767
-UM, IT SEEMED LIKE YOU WERE
ACTING A LITTLE STRANGE --

74
00:05:03,767 --> 00:05:04,867
WELL, REALLY STRANGE.

75
00:05:04,867 --> 00:05:06,767
ANYWAY, I MEAN,
THIS IS REALLY DANGEROUS.

76
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:07,767
-DANGEROUS?

77
00:05:07,767 --> 00:05:09,267
WHY WOULD IT BE?
-[ GASPS ]

78
00:05:09,267 --> 00:05:11,567
-AS YOU KNOW, I AM KRAEHE.

79
00:05:11,567 --> 00:05:13,467
-[ SIGHS ] YOU'RE RUE!

80
00:05:13,467 --> 00:05:16,601
-[ GASPS ]
-THAT'S WHO YOU ARE.

81
00:05:16,601 --> 00:05:19,167
THAT'S HOW...I THINK OF YOU.

82
00:05:19,167 --> 00:05:20,701
I MEAN -- [ SCREAMS ]

83
00:05:20,701 --> 00:05:21,901
THAT SCARED ME.

84
00:05:21,901 --> 00:05:24,467
-I'D SAY <i>YOU'RE</i> THE ONE
IN DANGER.

85
00:05:24,467 --> 00:05:27,267
-YEAH, SURE LOOKS THAT WAY, HUH?

86
00:05:27,267 --> 00:05:29,767
-I'M STILL...

87
00:05:29,767 --> 00:05:32,034
[ WIND HOWLING ]

88
00:05:32,034 --> 00:05:35,801
I'M STILL PRINCESS KRAEHE,
REGARDLESS.

89
00:05:40,201 --> 00:05:41,767
-B-BUT RUE...

90
00:05:47,734 --> 00:05:49,401
-Both: DUCK!
-HMM?

91
00:05:49,401 --> 00:05:51,401
-WERE IN THE HECK WERE YOU?!
-THIS IS AWFUL!

92
00:05:51,401 --> 00:05:52,401
-HUH?

93
00:05:52,401 --> 00:05:53,834
-POOR, POOR DUCK!
-WHOA!

94
00:05:53,834 --> 00:05:55,167
-AWW!
-I CAN'T BELIEVE

95
00:05:55,167 --> 00:05:57,134
YOU WOULD ACTUALLY
SKIP POINTE CLASS!

96
00:05:57,134 --> 00:05:58,301
-OH, WELL, YOU SEE...

97
00:05:58,301 --> 00:06:01,301
-HE'S COMING. HE'S COMING.
-[ WHIMPERING ]

98
00:06:01,301 --> 00:06:03,801
-DON'T BE SCARED.
-THAT'S SCARY.

99
00:06:03,801 --> 00:06:06,501
-NOW, DUCK,
JUST WRIGGLE YOUR WAY OUT OF IT.

100
00:06:06,501 --> 00:06:07,734
IT'S YOUR ONE HOPE.

101
00:06:07,734 --> 00:06:09,301
-HUH? OUT OF WHAT?
-HE'S HERE!

102
00:06:09,301 --> 00:06:10,567
-SO, HE'S COME.

103
00:06:10,567 --> 00:06:12,567
[ NECK CREAKING ]

104
00:06:12,567 --> 00:06:14,434
-[ GROANS ]

105
00:06:14,434 --> 00:06:18,701
-SO, MISS DUCK...IT'S TIME
WE BOTH HAD A LITTLE TALK.

106
00:06:18,701 --> 00:06:20,634
-IT'S FINALLY...

107
00:06:20,634 --> 00:06:22,367
-THE PROPOSAL.

108
00:06:22,367 --> 00:06:23,534
-WHAT?

109
00:06:23,534 --> 00:06:25,867
-HERE, DUCK,
I'LL HOLD YOUR BOOKS FOR YOU.

110
00:06:25,867 --> 00:06:27,201
-UM, UH, THANK YOU.

111
00:06:27,201 --> 00:06:29,867
-NOW GET OUT THERE
AND START WRIGGLING.

112
00:06:29,867 --> 00:06:31,067
-YEAH, UH, RIGHT.

113
00:06:31,067 --> 00:06:32,667
-MISS DUCK.

114
00:06:32,667 --> 00:06:34,234
-[ Fearfully ] YES, SIR?

115
00:06:34,234 --> 00:06:36,567
-EVERYBODY
HAS TIMES WHEN THEY FEEL

116
00:06:36,567 --> 00:06:39,734
AS IF THEY'LL NEVER BE ABLE
TO REACH THEIR DREAMS.

117
00:06:39,734 --> 00:06:41,101
-HUH?

118
00:06:41,101 --> 00:06:43,667
-HOWEVER, DECIDING THERE'S
NO WAY YOU CAN DO SOMETHING

119
00:06:43,667 --> 00:06:46,767
IS NOTHING MORE THAN A WAY
OF COMFORTING YOURSELF

120
00:06:46,767 --> 00:06:48,367
WHEN YOU LACK MOTIVATION.

121
00:06:48,367 --> 00:06:49,534
-[ GASPS ]

122
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:51,767
-ARE YOU POSITIVE
YOU'RE NOT FOOLING YOURSELF

123
00:06:51,767 --> 00:06:53,134
ABOUT HOW YOU FEEL,

124
00:06:53,134 --> 00:06:56,034
ABOUT WHAT IS EXACTLY
THE MOST IMPORTANT THING TO YOU

125
00:06:56,034 --> 00:06:57,401
IN THE WHOLE WORLD, MM?

126
00:06:57,401 --> 00:06:58,701
-[ SIGHS ]

127
00:06:59,767 --> 00:07:03,167
I DECIDED TO BECOME A GIRL
FOR MYTHO,

128
00:07:03,167 --> 00:07:06,567
AND I BECAME PRINCESS TUTU
FOR MYTHO.

129
00:07:06,567 --> 00:07:08,467
BUT SOMEWHERE, SOMEHOW,

130
00:07:08,467 --> 00:07:12,634
I CAME TO THE CONCLUSION
THAT I COULDN'T DO ANYTHING.

131
00:07:12,634 --> 00:07:14,067
AM I RUNNING AWAY?

132
00:07:14,067 --> 00:07:16,101
WHAT'S MOST IMPORTANT TO ME?

133
00:07:16,101 --> 00:07:17,734
-SO, IF PERCHANCE THIS DREAM

134
00:07:17,734 --> 00:07:20,701
YOU'VE BEEN SUPPRESSING
FAR TOO LONG IS TO MARRY ME

135
00:07:20,701 --> 00:07:22,934
AND YOUR HEART
ISN'T IN YOUR LESSONS

136
00:07:22,934 --> 00:07:25,901
BECAUSE YOU'RE AGONIZING
OVER THAT, THEN I, FOR MY PART,

137
00:07:25,901 --> 00:07:28,467
MUST RESERVE A PLACE
TO HOLD THE CEREMONY AT --

138
00:07:28,467 --> 00:07:29,501
AAH!

139
00:07:29,501 --> 00:07:30,901
-THANK YOU FOR ALL YOUR HELP,
MR. CAT.

140
00:07:30,901 --> 00:07:31,901
-[ MEOWS ]

141
00:07:31,901 --> 00:07:33,367
-GOODBYE NOW!
-GOODBYE?

142
00:07:33,367 --> 00:07:35,634
-[ GASPS ]
SHE SQUIRMED OUT OF IT!

143
00:07:35,634 --> 00:07:38,367
-IT'S A BIG SHOCK FOR MR. CAT.
-[ YOWLING ]

144
00:07:38,367 --> 00:07:40,634
-I CAN'T LET THINGS
STAY THIS WAY.

145
00:07:40,634 --> 00:07:42,567
I'LL SEARCH
FOR THE HEART SHARDS.

146
00:07:42,567 --> 00:07:43,934
I'LL SEARCH THE TOWN!

147
00:07:43,934 --> 00:07:45,834
THAT'S WHAT I CAN DO RIGHT NOW.

148
00:07:45,834 --> 00:07:47,667
IT'S WHAT I CAN DO FOR MYTHO!

149
00:07:52,767 --> 00:07:55,301
-[ SIGHS ]

150
00:07:57,934 --> 00:08:00,767
-ARE YOU THE RUE
WE'RE WORRIED ABOUT, ZURA?

151
00:08:00,767 --> 00:08:02,834
-WHAT?
-DUCK SAID THAT, ZURA.

152
00:08:02,834 --> 00:08:05,334
-WHAT? DUCK DID?

153
00:08:05,334 --> 00:08:08,201
I ALREADY TOLD YOU
THERE IS NO RUE.

154
00:08:08,201 --> 00:08:11,334
-THAT'S NOT TRUE.
I DON'T BELIEVE THAT!

155
00:08:11,334 --> 00:08:14,467
-I GET THIS FEELING
YOU'RE STILL RUE.

156
00:08:14,467 --> 00:08:15,467
YOU'RE RUE!

157
00:08:15,467 --> 00:08:16,701
-[ GASPS ]

158
00:08:16,701 --> 00:08:17,934
[ GASPS ]

159
00:08:17,934 --> 00:08:21,501
-HAVE I -- HAVE I MET YOU
SOMEWHERE BEFORE, ZURA?

160
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:23,601
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
I'VE NEVER MET A GIRL LIKE...

161
00:08:23,601 --> 00:08:26,101
-AH!

162
00:08:26,101 --> 00:08:28,234
-WHO...

163
00:08:28,234 --> 00:08:29,267
ARE YOU?

164
00:08:29,267 --> 00:08:31,367
-UZURA IS UZURA, ZURA.

165
00:08:31,367 --> 00:08:32,467
-SO DO...

166
00:08:32,467 --> 00:08:34,667
DO YOU ACTUALLY KNOW --

167
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:38,401
DO YOU KNOW
IF I'M REALLY THE CROW'S...

168
00:08:38,401 --> 00:08:39,967
THIS IS STUPID.

169
00:08:39,967 --> 00:08:43,534
I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR THIS NONSENSE.

170
00:08:43,534 --> 00:08:46,034
-THIS IS SOME SORT OF MISTAKE!

171
00:08:46,034 --> 00:08:47,334
[ RAPS TABLE ]

172
00:08:47,334 --> 00:08:49,701
SURE, WHEN I INVESTIGATED
DROSSELMEYER'S FAMILY TREE,

173
00:08:49,701 --> 00:08:51,167
HE WAS A DIRECT DESCENDANT,

174
00:08:51,167 --> 00:08:53,234
BUT HE WAS ONLY ABLE
TO FIND THAT OUT

175
00:08:53,234 --> 00:08:56,134
THANKS TO MY TAKING NOTE OF HIM
AND SHOWING HIM MYSELF.

176
00:08:56,134 --> 00:09:00,134
I EVEN KNOW WHO YOU PEOPLE ARE!

177
00:09:00,134 --> 00:09:01,767
I AM FAR MORE QUALIFIED.

178
00:09:01,767 --> 00:09:04,334
I WANT YOU PEOPLE
TO ACKNOWLEDGE ME,

179
00:09:04,334 --> 00:09:06,801
YOU WHO ARE
THE STOPPERS OF STORIES,

180
00:09:06,801 --> 00:09:08,434
THE SO-CALLED "BOOK MEN."

181
00:09:08,434 --> 00:09:11,101
-THERE AREN'T ANY QUALIFICATIONS
TO BEING HUMAN.

182
00:09:11,101 --> 00:09:12,334
-THAT'S NOT MY POINT!

183
00:09:12,334 --> 00:09:13,967
IS THIS WORLD UNDER THE CONTROL

184
00:09:13,967 --> 00:09:15,867
OF DROSSELMEYER'S STORIES
OR NOT?

185
00:09:15,867 --> 00:09:18,634
WHETHER LIVING IN THIS WORLD
HINDERS OUR DISCERNMENT

186
00:09:18,634 --> 00:09:19,834
DOESN'T MATTER TO ME.

187
00:09:19,834 --> 00:09:22,101
I WANT TO KNOW THE TRUTH
OF THIS MYSTERY!

188
00:09:22,101 --> 00:09:24,434
-THERE ARE THINGS
IT'S OKAY TO KNOW

189
00:09:24,434 --> 00:09:25,701
AND THINGS THAT IT'S NOT.

190
00:09:25,701 --> 00:09:26,701
GO HOME.

191
00:09:26,701 --> 00:09:29,601
-[ GRUNTS ] DAMN IT.

192
00:09:33,901 --> 00:09:36,434
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

193
00:09:41,434 --> 00:09:43,934
-LET'S CUT THAT BOY'S HANDS OFF,
TOO.

194
00:09:43,934 --> 00:09:46,267
-JUST LIKE WE DID
TO DROSSELMEYER.

195
00:09:46,267 --> 00:09:49,434
-LET'S CUT THEM OFF BEFORE
HE STARTS WRITING STORIES.

196
00:09:49,434 --> 00:09:50,434
-PATIENCE.

197
00:09:50,434 --> 00:09:53,534
AS BOOK MEN,
OUR TIME IS TOO PRECIOUS

198
00:09:53,534 --> 00:09:57,367
TO BE WASTING IT
ON FIGHTING FALSE STORYTELLERS.

199
00:09:57,367 --> 00:09:58,834
-THEN LET'S GET THE ONE

200
00:09:58,834 --> 00:10:01,267
WHO EXCHANGES WORDS
WITH THE OAK TREE.

201
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:02,434
-HMM.

202
00:10:02,434 --> 00:10:05,001
-WHAT ON EARTH AM I DOING?

203
00:10:05,001 --> 00:10:08,934
FATHER IS SEEKING A HEART,
AND YET I...

204
00:10:08,934 --> 00:10:10,001
-DAMN IT.

205
00:10:10,001 --> 00:10:11,634
SO, FAKIR, HE'S THE ONE, IS HE?

206
00:10:11,634 --> 00:10:13,867
THEN WHAT WAS I BORN INTO
THIS WORLD FOR?

207
00:10:13,867 --> 00:10:15,534
WHAT WOULD --
[ THUD ] HUH?

208
00:10:16,801 --> 00:10:19,834
HMM?
-SO COLD.

209
00:10:21,834 --> 00:10:23,601
-WHAT'S WRONG?

210
00:10:23,601 --> 00:10:24,967
-[ SIGHS ]

211
00:10:24,967 --> 00:10:27,534
-YOU'RE RUE
FROM THE BALLET DIVISION.

212
00:10:27,534 --> 00:10:30,501
-[ SIGHS ]
-[ GASPS ]

213
00:10:33,234 --> 00:10:35,701
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

214
00:10:46,401 --> 00:10:48,201
-SOMEWHERE IN THIS TOWN --

215
00:10:48,201 --> 00:10:51,167
THERE'S GOT TO BE A HEART SHARD
SOMEWHERE.

216
00:10:51,167 --> 00:10:52,234
[ GASPS ]

217
00:10:54,501 --> 00:10:57,434
QUACK!

218
00:10:57,434 --> 00:10:58,601
-WHO'S THERE?

219
00:10:58,601 --> 00:11:03,834
-JUST NOW MYTHO'S SHADOW
LOOKED LIKE A CROW!

220
00:11:03,834 --> 00:11:06,234
-BE CAREFUL, LITTLE DUCK.

221
00:11:06,234 --> 00:11:09,867
BECAUSE
FOR THE STOPPERS OF STORIES,

222
00:11:09,867 --> 00:11:15,167
BEHEADING A DEFENSELESS LITTLE
DUCK IS MERE CHILD'S PLAY.

223
00:11:15,167 --> 00:11:17,301
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

224
00:11:34,424 --> 00:11:36,224
-[ GASPS ]
WHAT SHOULD I DO?!

225
00:11:36,224 --> 00:11:38,157
[ WHIMPERING ]

226
00:11:38,157 --> 00:11:39,424
OKAY.

227
00:11:39,424 --> 00:11:44,557
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK, QUACK,
QUACK, QUACK. QUACK?

228
00:11:44,557 --> 00:11:47,457
QUACK? WHAT?

229
00:11:47,457 --> 00:11:50,890
-SAY, WHAT HAPPENED
TO ALL THE OTHER BIRDS?

230
00:11:50,890 --> 00:11:54,024
THEY JUST WON'T COME
WHEN I CALL THEM.

231
00:11:54,024 --> 00:11:55,524
-MYTHO? QUACK.

232
00:11:55,524 --> 00:11:56,690
-STRANGE, ISN'T IT?

233
00:11:56,690 --> 00:11:59,057
WHEN HERE,
I LOVE EVERYONE IN THE WORLD

234
00:11:59,057 --> 00:12:00,524
AND WANT TO PROTECT THEM.

235
00:12:00,524 --> 00:12:02,924
-[ GASPS ] THE PRINCE'S HEART!

236
00:12:02,924 --> 00:12:08,024
-BUT I ALSO WANT TO MAKE
ALL THE WORLD'S LOVE MY OWN.

237
00:12:08,024 --> 00:12:11,424
-[ SIGHS ]
-I WONDER WHICH IS THE REAL ME.

238
00:12:11,424 --> 00:12:13,424
I WANT PEOPLE TO LOVE ME.

239
00:12:13,424 --> 00:12:15,924
BUT IS IT OKAY TO JUST BE LOVED?

240
00:12:15,924 --> 00:12:17,124
I DON'T KNOW.

241
00:12:17,124 --> 00:12:20,057
MY PRIDE
IS STILL LOST IN THE DARK.

242
00:12:20,057 --> 00:12:23,790
I MUST OVERCOME
THIS RAVEN'S BLOOD IN ME

243
00:12:23,790 --> 00:12:26,590
AND UPHOLD MY PRIDE AS A PRINCE.

244
00:12:26,590 --> 00:12:30,357
IT IS MY DUTY
TO PROTECT ALL THE PEOPLE.

245
00:12:31,857 --> 00:12:34,490
I WANT MY HEART TO BE WHOLE
SO...

246
00:12:34,490 --> 00:12:35,924
-QUACK. MYTHO.

247
00:12:35,924 --> 00:12:38,190
ONCE I HAVE ALL THE SHARDS
OF MY HEART BACK...

248
00:12:38,190 --> 00:12:39,424
[ CHUCKLES ]

249
00:12:39,424 --> 00:12:42,990
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S
"WALTZ OF THE FLOWERS" PLAYS ]

250
00:12:44,590 --> 00:12:47,290
-[ Voice breaking ]
I'M SORRY, MYTHO.

251
00:12:47,290 --> 00:12:50,457
I SWORE TO GET
ALL OF YOUR HEART BACK, BUT...

252
00:12:50,457 --> 00:12:52,624
I'M SORRY. I'M GONNA DO MY BEST.

253
00:12:52,624 --> 00:12:55,057
THEY MUST BE SOMEWHERE
IN THIS TOWN.

254
00:12:55,057 --> 00:12:57,324
I WILL FIND THEM, I WILL!

255
00:12:57,324 --> 00:13:00,990
I'LL CERTAINLY,
DEFINITELY, ABSOLUTELY,

256
00:13:00,990 --> 00:13:02,957
POSITIVELY FIND THEM!

257
00:13:02,957 --> 00:13:04,457
BECAUSE THAT'S ALL I CAN DO!

258
00:13:04,457 --> 00:13:07,457
-[ GASPING ]

259
00:13:10,524 --> 00:13:12,590
-I CAN FEEL YOUR HEART BEATING.

260
00:13:12,590 --> 00:13:13,824
IT'S RATHER FAST.

261
00:13:13,824 --> 00:13:14,824
WHY IS THAT?

262
00:13:14,824 --> 00:13:16,924
-BECAUSE YOU'RE --
[ GASPS ]

263
00:13:16,924 --> 00:13:18,724
So fragrant.

264
00:13:18,724 --> 00:13:22,890
[ HEART BEATING ]

265
00:13:22,890 --> 00:13:23,990
[ GASPS ]

266
00:13:23,990 --> 00:13:25,824
-COME WITH ME.

267
00:13:25,824 --> 00:13:28,857
-OKAY.

268
00:13:28,857 --> 00:13:30,524
-[ PANTING ]

269
00:13:34,157 --> 00:13:36,157
[ GRUNTING ]
WHOA!

270
00:13:37,657 --> 00:13:38,657
WHOA!

271
00:13:38,657 --> 00:13:39,824
-WHO ARE YOU?

272
00:13:39,824 --> 00:13:41,590
-WE ARE THE BOOK MEN.

273
00:13:41,590 --> 00:13:45,224
IF YOU INTEND TO EMPLOY
DROSSELMEYER'S POWER

274
00:13:45,224 --> 00:13:49,657
TO SPIN STORIES YOURSELF,
WE WILL BE FORCED TO STOP YOU.

275
00:13:49,657 --> 00:13:51,257
-THE BOOK MEN?

276
00:13:51,257 --> 00:13:54,624
-OUR ANCESTORS CUT OFF
DROSSELMEYER'S HANDS

277
00:13:54,624 --> 00:13:58,257
AND MADE HIM UNABLE
TO SPIN STORIES EVER AGAIN.

278
00:13:58,257 --> 00:14:01,690
SHOULD HIS DESCENDANT
EVER TRY TO SPIN A STORY,

279
00:14:01,690 --> 00:14:03,890
WE MUST DEAL HIM THE SAME FATE.

280
00:14:03,890 --> 00:14:05,190
THAT IS THE DUTY

281
00:14:05,190 --> 00:14:08,757
THAT HAS BEEN PASSED DOWN TO US
OVER GENERATIONS.

282
00:14:08,757 --> 00:14:11,090
-SO YOU'RE GOING TO
CUT OFF MY HANDS, THEN?

283
00:14:11,090 --> 00:14:13,724
-DANGEROUS STORIES
MUST NOT BE BORN.

284
00:14:13,724 --> 00:14:15,457
WE MUST STOP THE STORIES

285
00:14:15,457 --> 00:14:19,090
THAT ALREADY HAVE BEEN BORN
BY BURYING THEIR ENDINGS.

286
00:14:19,090 --> 00:14:20,124
-[ GASPS ] WHAT?

287
00:14:20,124 --> 00:14:21,357
YOU'RE THE ONES RESPONSIBLE

288
00:14:21,357 --> 00:14:23,090
FOR TEARING OUT
THE STORIES' ENDINGS?

289
00:14:23,090 --> 00:14:24,990
-COME.

290
00:14:24,990 --> 00:14:27,624
-[ PANTING ]

291
00:14:27,624 --> 00:14:29,257
[ SIGHS ]

292
00:14:29,257 --> 00:14:31,157
[ PANTING ]

293
00:14:31,157 --> 00:14:34,024
I'M NOT GONNA GIVE UP YET.
I STILL GOT A --

294
00:14:34,024 --> 00:14:35,124
[ GASPS ] WHAT?

295
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:37,824
A HEART SHARD! WHERE?! WHERE?!

296
00:14:37,824 --> 00:14:41,024
OH! MAYBE IT'S ON
THE OTHER SIDE OF THIS GATE?

297
00:14:41,024 --> 00:14:42,990
[ Straining ] WHY WON'T IT...

298
00:14:42,990 --> 00:14:43,990
[ GRUNTING ]

299
00:14:43,990 --> 00:14:45,724
COME ON! OPEN UP!

300
00:14:45,724 --> 00:14:47,057
[ GRUNTING ]

301
00:14:47,057 --> 00:14:48,257
OHH!

302
00:14:48,257 --> 00:14:49,657
HMM, IT WON'T OPEN. HUH.

303
00:14:49,657 --> 00:14:51,757
I WONDER
IF THERE ARE OTHER EXITS.

304
00:14:53,924 --> 00:14:55,490
-WE'RE FINALLY HERE, AREN'T WE?

305
00:14:55,490 --> 00:14:56,690
-Both: YEAH!
-HUH?

306
00:14:56,690 --> 00:14:58,990
-SO, THIS IS GOLD CROWN TOWN.
-WHAT?

307
00:14:58,990 --> 00:15:01,257
WAS MOM ALWAYS
AN INDIAN RHINOCEROS?

308
00:15:01,257 --> 00:15:02,724
-YOU KNOW, YOU'RE RIGHT.

309
00:15:02,724 --> 00:15:06,357
BEFORE WE GOT TO THIS TOWN, NAH,
THERE'S NO WAY THAT COULD BE.

310
00:15:06,357 --> 00:15:08,590
-COME ON,
OR I'LL LEAVE YOU BEHIND.

311
00:15:08,590 --> 00:15:10,990
-YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.
-Both: YES, MOM.

312
00:15:10,990 --> 00:15:13,357
-THE GATE DIDN'T OPEN JUST NOW,
DID IT?

313
00:15:13,357 --> 00:15:16,024
IT WAS LIKE THEY JUST
SUDDENLY APPEARED THERE.

314
00:15:16,024 --> 00:15:19,324
-A STORY'S BIRTH
IS A SUDDEN EVENT --

315
00:15:19,324 --> 00:15:21,524
A START, A HAPPY ACCIDENT.

316
00:15:21,524 --> 00:15:22,724
-[ GASPS ]

317
00:15:22,724 --> 00:15:25,424
SO WERE THEY...SUDDENLY
BORN FROM THE GATE?

318
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:29,024
-YES, THIS TOWN IS MOST LIKELY
CONTROLLED BY STORIES.

319
00:15:29,024 --> 00:15:32,257
YET WE ARE UNABLE
TO REALIZE THIS FACT.

320
00:15:32,257 --> 00:15:35,657
BECAUSE WE'RE MADE TO BELIEVE
THAT WHATEVER WE SEE,

321
00:15:35,657 --> 00:15:38,990
NO MATTER HOW STRANGE,
WAS THAT WAY TO BEGIN WITH.

322
00:15:38,990 --> 00:15:41,724
NO ONE BUT I
CAN DISSECT THIS MYSTERY.

323
00:15:41,724 --> 00:15:45,857
THEREFORE, I AM THE ONE WHO'S
QUALIFIED TO CHANGE THE WORLD.

324
00:15:45,857 --> 00:15:47,290
HUH?
-YOU'RE RIGHT.

325
00:15:47,290 --> 00:15:50,090
YOU DO HAVE WHAT IT TAKES
TO CHANGE THE WORLD.

326
00:15:50,090 --> 00:15:52,857
-I SEE. YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT I'M SAYING, THEN.

327
00:15:52,857 --> 00:15:54,924
-SINCE YOU'LL BECOME
THE BLOOD AND FLESH

328
00:15:54,924 --> 00:15:56,857
OF THE ONE
WHO WILL CHANGE THE WORLD.

329
00:15:56,857 --> 00:15:59,857
-WHAT A TRULY MAGNIFICENT GIRL
YOU ARE.

330
00:15:59,857 --> 00:16:02,424
-THIS WAY.
-RUE, WAIT UP!

331
00:16:02,424 --> 00:16:03,947
WHERE ARE YOU TAKING ME?

332
00:16:09,429 --> 00:16:14,429
-SOMEWHERE -- THERE'S GOT TO BE
ANOTHER EXIT SOMEWHERE.

333
00:16:14,429 --> 00:16:16,529
I KNOW IT!

334
00:16:16,529 --> 00:16:18,929
[ GRUNTING ]

335
00:16:18,929 --> 00:16:20,696
IT'S NO GOOD.

336
00:16:20,696 --> 00:16:22,363
WHAT? AGAIN?

337
00:16:22,363 --> 00:16:23,396
[ GASPS ]

338
00:16:26,329 --> 00:16:28,129
WHAT DOES THIS MEAN?

339
00:16:28,129 --> 00:16:31,529
WHAT'S ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THIS GATE?

340
00:16:31,529 --> 00:16:33,063
[ PANTING ]

341
00:16:33,063 --> 00:16:34,796
[ NECKLACE DINGS ]

342
00:16:34,796 --> 00:16:36,129
THIS ONE TOO!

343
00:16:36,129 --> 00:16:38,863
[ PANTING ]

344
00:16:38,863 --> 00:16:40,163
AND HERE.

345
00:16:43,029 --> 00:16:45,763
[ PANTING ]

346
00:16:52,629 --> 00:16:54,029
[ SIGHS ]

347
00:16:54,029 --> 00:16:57,629
THERE MUST BE HEART SHARDS
SOMEWHERE OUTSIDE THESE GATES!

348
00:16:57,629 --> 00:16:59,863
[ TWINKLING, BUBBLING ]

349
00:17:13,629 --> 00:17:17,463
HEART SHARDS, WHERE ARE YOU?

350
00:17:17,463 --> 00:17:18,929
-[ GASPS ]

351
00:17:25,363 --> 00:17:26,796
-WHAT?

352
00:17:26,796 --> 00:17:29,796
A WALL?

353
00:17:29,796 --> 00:17:30,796
[ GASPS ]

354
00:17:30,796 --> 00:17:32,896
-[ GASPS ]
WHAT IS THIS?

355
00:17:32,896 --> 00:17:36,863
-THE GRAVE OF THE MAN
WHO PLAYED WITH STORIES AT WILL,

356
00:17:36,863 --> 00:17:40,529
WHO BROKE DOWN THE WALL
BETWEEN REALITY AND STORY

357
00:17:40,529 --> 00:17:43,229
AND PLAYED WITH THE FATES
OF LIVING PEOPLE.

358
00:17:43,229 --> 00:17:45,029
-THIS IS DROSSELMEYER'S GRAVE.

359
00:17:45,029 --> 00:17:49,529
-WE'LL CUT OFF BOTH YOUR HANDS
AND SEAL THEM HERE.

360
00:17:49,529 --> 00:17:51,129
[ CHUCKLES CRUELLY ]

361
00:17:53,296 --> 00:17:56,496
-THE OUTSIDE OF GOLD CROWN TOWN
IS NOTHING BUT WALLS?

362
00:17:57,763 --> 00:17:58,763
[ GASPS ]

363
00:17:58,763 --> 00:17:59,763
-[ Straining ] STOP!

364
00:17:59,763 --> 00:18:01,229
LET GO OFF ME, DAMN YOU!

365
00:18:01,229 --> 00:18:03,263
I HAVE TO WRITE!

366
00:18:03,263 --> 00:18:05,463
[ GRUNTING ]

367
00:18:07,496 --> 00:18:08,663
-STOP!

368
00:18:08,663 --> 00:18:10,496
-Together: HUH?

369
00:18:12,796 --> 00:18:15,096
[ ALL GRUNT ]

370
00:18:15,096 --> 00:18:18,063
-[ GASPS ] PRINCESS TUTU?!

371
00:18:20,096 --> 00:18:23,829
THIS IS...

372
00:18:23,829 --> 00:18:25,829
-THANK YOU.

373
00:18:25,829 --> 00:18:27,796
-I'M SO GLAD.

374
00:18:27,796 --> 00:18:29,329
[ GASPS ]
[ GEARS CLINKING ]

375
00:18:29,329 --> 00:18:31,496
-[ GASPS ]
-HUH? WHAT IS THIS?

376
00:18:31,496 --> 00:18:34,196
-WHAT'S THIS?
WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON?

377
00:18:34,196 --> 00:18:36,296
-IT'S DANGEROUS TO SHOW YOURSELF

378
00:18:36,296 --> 00:18:39,329
BEFORE THOSE REPUGNANT PEOPLE,
PRINCESS TUTU.

379
00:18:39,329 --> 00:18:41,529
-[ GASPS ]
DROSSELMEYER DID THAT?

380
00:18:44,129 --> 00:18:46,296
-IN THE END,
EVERYONE'S A MARIONETTE.

381
00:18:46,296 --> 00:18:50,796
AT THE MOMENT,
I FEEL SOMEWHAT AT A LOSS.

382
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:53,296
SEEMS I'VE...

383
00:18:53,296 --> 00:18:56,963
IS THIS SOMETHING THAT THE STORY
HAS DECIDED, AS WELL?

384
00:18:56,963 --> 00:18:59,529
SEEMS I'VE FALLEN IN LOVE
WITH YOU.

385
00:18:59,529 --> 00:19:02,529
-[ GASPS ] WITH ME?

386
00:19:02,529 --> 00:19:03,763
-YES.

387
00:19:03,763 --> 00:19:07,263
-ENOUGH TO SACRIFICE YOUR LIFE?

388
00:19:07,263 --> 00:19:09,496
-YES, IF IT IS FOR YOUR SAKE.

389
00:19:09,496 --> 00:19:11,196
-[ GASPS ]

390
00:19:11,196 --> 00:19:14,729
[ GIGGLES ]

391
00:19:14,729 --> 00:19:16,896
[ LAUGHS ]

392
00:19:16,896 --> 00:19:19,663
THERE'S NO WAY WHAT
YOU'RE SAYING COULD BE TRUE.

393
00:19:19,663 --> 00:19:20,963
-IT IS! LISTEN!

394
00:19:20,963 --> 00:19:22,296
-STOP IT!

395
00:19:22,296 --> 00:19:25,963
-THERE'S NO WAY THAT I CAN STOP
FROM LOVING YOU NOW.

396
00:19:25,963 --> 00:19:28,429
-JUST GO HOME.

397
00:19:31,029 --> 00:19:33,696
-THIS EMOTION ISN'T FAKE.

398
00:19:37,896 --> 00:19:39,129
-[ Voice breaking ]
I'M SORRY, FATHER,

399
00:19:39,129 --> 00:19:42,529
FOR BEING A BAD DAUGHTER,

400
00:19:42,529 --> 00:19:45,696
BUT I-I COULDN'T DO IT.

401
00:19:45,696 --> 00:19:48,196
-YOU'RE THAT MAN
FROM THE USED BOOKSTORE.

402
00:19:48,196 --> 00:19:50,496
-BEFORE DROSSELMEYER
LOST HIS HANDS,

403
00:19:50,496 --> 00:19:53,396
HE'D ALREADY MADE A DEVICE
THAT WOULD ENABLE HIM

404
00:19:53,396 --> 00:19:58,229
TO CONTINUE WEAVING STORIES
EVEN IF HE LOST HIS BODY.

405
00:19:58,229 --> 00:20:01,863
THE TOWN IS BEING CONTROLLED BY
STORIES BECAUSE OF THAT DEVICE.

406
00:20:01,863 --> 00:20:04,696
BUT EVEN WE CAN'T DISCOVER
WHICH PARTS ARE REAL

407
00:20:04,696 --> 00:20:06,063
AND WHICH ARE FICTION!

408
00:20:06,063 --> 00:20:08,296
HOWEVER, PRINCESS TUTU,

409
00:20:08,296 --> 00:20:12,096
WHO NO ONE INSIDE DROSSELMEYER'S
STORIES WAS EXPECTED TO BECOME,

410
00:20:12,096 --> 00:20:15,229
APPEARED
AND TRIED TO PROTECT YOU.

411
00:20:15,229 --> 00:20:19,529
AND PRINCESS TUTU WAS TAKEN
CAPTIVE BY DROSSELMEYER.

412
00:20:19,529 --> 00:20:21,396
BY NOW THE STORY
MAY HAVE PROGRESSED

413
00:20:21,396 --> 00:20:23,296
TO THE POINT
WHERE WE CAN DO NOTHING.

414
00:20:23,296 --> 00:20:25,296
IN THAT CASE,
THE ONLY ONE WHO CAN FIGHT

415
00:20:25,296 --> 00:20:27,029
IS HE WHO CARRIES
THE SAME BLOOD.

416
00:20:27,029 --> 00:20:30,063
-SO THE ONE I'M UP AGAINST
ISN'T THE RAVEN?

417
00:20:30,063 --> 00:20:33,529
DROSSELMEYER'S STORY ITSELF
IS MY ACTUAL ADVERSARY?

418
00:20:33,529 --> 00:20:35,029
-MAY WE BELIEVE, THEN,

419
00:20:35,029 --> 00:20:38,529
THAT YOU ARE NOT SOMEONE
WHO PLAYS AROUND WITH STORIES?

420
00:20:38,529 --> 00:20:41,496
-YOU KNOW, THERE'S STILL
SOMETHING I FEEL I'M LACKING.

421
00:20:41,496 --> 00:20:43,863
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT IT IS I'M LACKING,

422
00:20:43,863 --> 00:20:45,529
SO I CAN'T EVEN START WRITING.

423
00:20:45,529 --> 00:20:48,363
-THERE'S NOTHING WE CAN DO
TO HELP YOU THERE.

424
00:20:48,363 --> 00:20:50,963
THAT IS A WALL
YOU WILL HAVE TO SURMOUNT.

425
00:20:50,963 --> 00:20:54,429
IF YOU ATTEMPT TO LEAD THE STORY
DOWN AN ABOMINABLE PATH,

426
00:20:54,429 --> 00:20:57,529
WE WILL BE FORCED
TO CARRY OUT OUR DUTY ONCE MORE.

427
00:20:57,529 --> 00:21:00,363
YOU WILL DO WELL
TO REMEMBER THAT.

428
00:21:05,763 --> 00:21:08,363
DROSSELMEYER.

429
00:21:08,363 --> 00:21:09,963
THE MAN WHO PLAYS WANTONLY

430
00:21:09,963 --> 00:21:12,596
WITH THE FATES OF MYTHO
AND EVERYONE ELSE.

431
00:21:12,596 --> 00:21:15,596
DO I REALLY POSSESS ENOUGH POWER
IN ME TO FIGHT WITH HIM?

432
00:21:15,596 --> 00:21:18,396
[ GEARS CLICKING ]
CAN I SAVE MYTHO?

433
00:21:18,396 --> 00:21:20,096
CAN I BRING TUTU BACK?

434
00:21:20,096 --> 00:21:22,363
-YOU'LL FIGHT WITH ME,
YOU SAY,

435
00:21:22,363 --> 00:21:24,263
YOU WHO ARE INSIDE THE STORY?

436
00:21:24,263 --> 00:21:25,663
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

437
00:21:25,663 --> 00:21:29,729
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN BEST IF YOU'D
BEEN TORN IN TWO RIGHT AWAY!

438
00:21:29,729 --> 00:21:32,963
AFTER ALL THIS TIME,
IT GRINDS TO A HALT NOW?

439
00:21:32,963 --> 00:21:35,096
I SUPPOSE THERE'S NO HELPING IT

440
00:21:35,096 --> 00:21:37,729
WITHOUT PRINCESS TUTU
IN THE STORY.

441
00:21:37,729 --> 00:21:39,563
OH, I MUST GET IT RUNNING!

442
00:21:39,563 --> 00:21:43,563
NOT GOOD, NOT GOOD AT ALL.
OHH!

443
00:21:50,563 --> 00:21:51,563
-OH.

444
00:21:51,563 --> 00:21:53,063
[ GASPS ]

445
00:21:53,063 --> 00:21:56,096
WHERE...

446
00:21:56,096 --> 00:21:58,729
IS THERE ANYBODY HERE?!

447
00:22:02,129 --> 00:22:06,363
WHERE...AM I?

448
00:22:06,363 --> 00:22:10,229
[ "ALTHOUGH MY LOVE IS SMALL"
PLAYS ]

449
00:22:19,763 --> 00:22:21,829
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

450
00:23:36,896 --> 00:23:39,329
-IF I THRUST THIS SWORD
INTO THE PRINCE, HE MIGHT DIE.

451
00:23:39,329 --> 00:23:42,863
THAT'S FINE.
IF THAT HAPPENS, I, TOO, WILL --

452
00:23:42,863 --> 00:23:45,496
-IS THIS THE WORLD
WHERE DROSSELMEYER IS?

453
00:23:45,496 --> 00:23:47,329
-THAT'S THE PRINCE
BACK WHEN I FIRST MET HIM.

454
00:23:47,329 --> 00:23:49,029
-YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ANYMORE.

455
00:23:49,029 --> 00:23:51,729
-[ Crying ] I-I'M NOT A CROW!
I'M A-A PERSON!

456
00:23:51,729 --> 00:23:54,096
I'M K-- RAE, REE, RU-- RUE.

457
00:23:54,096 --> 00:23:55,163
MY NAME IS RUE!

458
00:23:55,163 --> 00:23:56,396
-I CAN WRITE.

459
00:23:56,396 --> 00:23:57,996
I CAN WRITE A STORY ABOUT HER!

460
00:23:57,996 --> 00:24:00,496
-I AM A PUPPET
WHO COULD NOT HAVE A HEART.

461
00:24:00,496 --> 00:24:03,396
-ALL YOU CHILDREN
WHO LOVE STORIES,

462
00:24:03,396 --> 00:24:04,996
COME GATHER 'ROUND.

463
00:24:04,996 --> 00:24:06,029
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

